quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  16,27,"Then on the Day of Resurrection, He will disgrace them and will say, “Where are My [so-called] partners for whose sake you used to oppose [the truth]?” Those who were given knowledge will say, “Today disgrace and misery will befall the disbelievers.”",""
  16,28,"Those whose souls are seized by the angels while they wrong themselves will then offer submission, “We did not do anything evil.” “Yes, indeed you did! Allah knows well what you used to do.",""
  16,29,"So enter the gates of Hell, abiding therein forever. What a terrible abode for those who were arrogant!”",""
  16,30,"And it will be said to those who fear Allah, “What has your Lord sent down?” They will say, “All that is good.” For those who do good in this world, there is a good reward<sup>17</sup>; and the home of the Hereafter is far better. What an excellent home for those who fear Allah!","[17] Of a plentiful and satisfying life in this world."
  16,31,"They will enter the Gardens of Eternity, under which rivers flow. They will have therein whatever they wish<sup>18</sup>. This is how Allah rewards those who fear Him,","[18] Unlike this worldly life."
  16,32,"those whose souls the angels take while they are in a state of purity<sup>19</sup>, saying, “Peace be upon you; enter Paradise for what you used to do.”","[19] Their souls will be purified from polytheism, sins, and ill feelings."
  16,33,"Are [the disbelievers] waiting for the angels to come to them<sup>20</sup> or for the command of your Lord to come<sup>21</sup>? Those who came before them did the same. It was not Allah Who wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves.","[20] To take their souls while they are unjust to themselves.\n [21] To punish them in this worldly life."
  16,34,"They were afflicted by the evil consequences of their deeds, and they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule.",""
